  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Quantity Surveyor",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Education &\nExperience</strong></u></p><p>Diploma / Degree in Quantity Surveying, Construction\nManagement, Engineering or related field.</p><p>Minimum 2 years of experience using AutoCAD / Ravid /\nNavisworks for construction or M&E drawings.</p><p>At least 2 years of relevant on-site experience in\nconstruction, M&E, or industrial projects.</p><p><u><strong>Technical Skills</strong></u></p><p>Proficient in AutoCAD / Ravid / Navisworks for measurement,\ndrawing review, and quantity extraction.</p><p>Strong working knowledge of Microsoft Excel (costing,\nformulas, tables, analysis, reports).</p><p>Familiar with BOQ, cost breakdowns, variation claims, and\nprogress billing.</p><p>Experience in contract administration and cost control is an\nadvantage.</p><p><u><strong>Soft Skills</strong></u></p><p>Strong numerical, analytical and organizational skills.</p><p>Good communication and coordination skills.</p><p>Able to work independently and manage multiple tasks under\ntight timelines.</p><p>Attention to detail and strong commercial awareness.</p><p><u><strong>Preferred\n(Advantage)</strong></u></p><p>Experience in mechanical piping, semiconductor, or\nindustrial construction projects.</p><p>Familiar with piping material standards and its application.</p><p>Knowledge in Chilled water system, UPW system, Process\nSystem, Steel Structural, Plumbing & Sanitary.</p><p>Experience working in fast-track or high-tech construction\nenvironments</p>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 2,
